This needs to be reworded. This option will be used to ensure that the VPD is properly defaulted in the FRU stock, not used after the fact that the backplane has stale VPD.
A lot of lines are wrapped here, please fix. Also, please remove things like system names from the commit message.
It isn't clear to me what --force does. Why would a user want to use force? Just to not get that y/n option? Then I think the option needs to be renamed, maybe -y to say assume yes to answers.
The parent commit needs to go away I think and this needs to be reworked.
Please don't do checks like these. Let us pick one, say "yes" and stick with that.

nit: try to use uint8_t when just returning a value which can fit in 8 bits.

This is actually equal to "Parsed" type whichis defined in Store.hpp which is actually included in your code via impl.hpp. 
You can use "Parsed" here. Makes the code more readable. Anyways your call.
I don't prefer making vpd-tool depend on store.hpp file just for this alias. If Parsed moved to const file, then we can take a call. For now leaving it as it is.
It is already dependent on Store.hpp as it has impl.hpp which in-turn depends on Store.hpp. But ok.
